japanese beetles are eating up my birch tree what do i do hi some tips do not get a trap they bring more beetles to your yard than they kill so you end up with more damage now you can buy traps for all your neighbors with the hopes that your beetles will then go to their yards the easiest thing is to do nothing although it looks bad beetles usually don't do enough damage to cause any real harm to the tree if you really want to kill them spray them there are two types of spray to use a spray like sevin will kill the beetles that come in contact with it but it will wash off a systemic insect killer will be absorbed into the leaves and keep killing don't use this on fruit trees good luck Biological pest control Diseases of the honeybee Gypsy moth Apple Spider Fire fighting Pine Volkswagen Beetle Beetle in an Anthill Carnivorous plant Son Goku (Dragon Ball) Fecal incontinence 613 mitzvot Timon and Pumbaa Hamster Mosquito Tomato Quake III Arena Diablo II: Lord of Destruction Pollination Christmas tree Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Conker's Bad Fur Day Organic farming Naruto jutsu Tobacco Hay fever Cladistics Eutheism, dystheism, and maltheism Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Bark beetle Stag beetle Durian Pysanka Oak Ivy Wood Ultimate Spider-Man Big Bad Beetleborgs Jewel beetle Birch Pesticide USS Thresher (SS-200) Irreducible complexity Shotgun Snake Vermicompost Ragwort Ume Camp Lazlo Customs and etiquette of Japan Waking the Dragons Infinite Crisis Fuzion Garden Strawberry Callisto (Xena) Age of Mythology Turok: Dinosaur Hunter Peach Beetle (comics) Asian lady beetle RuneScape skills RuneScape quests Herbicide Seijuu Sentai Gingaman Venus Flytrap Insect Insect collecting Elephant Pepper spray Jet Force Gemini Resident Evil (video game) Mario series enemies Phoebe Halliwell Pikmin Drag racing Bonsai Shen Gong Wu Video game controversy Sharon Tate Tenchi Muyo! Totally Spies! Condom Animal Crossing Dutch elm disease Yu-Gi-Oh! anime, manga or movie only charact